<subSubSection pageId="90" pageNumber="91" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="90.[151,1437,1544,1787]" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,280,1544,1570]" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Comments</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schrottky" authorityYear="1906" box="[295,562,1544,1570]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Augochloropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="euryale">
<emphasis box="[295,562,1544,1570]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Augochloropsis euryale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was transferred to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1853" box="[781,930,1544,1570]" class="Insecta" family="Hymenoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Oxystoglossa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[781,930,1544,1570]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Oxystoglossa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Schrottky, C." box="[975,1168,1544,1570]" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" pagination="180 - 286" refId="ref76809" refString="Schrottky, C. (1913) La distribucion geografica de los himenopteros argentinos. Anales de La Sociedad Cientifica Argentina, 75, 180 - 286" type="journal article" year="1913">Schrottky (1913)</bibRefCitation>
, now a junior synonym of 
<emphasis box="[185,380,1580,1606]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1853" box="[185,317,1580,1606]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Augochlora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">Augochlora</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[328,380,1581,1606]" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" sensu="stricto">s.str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, and later 
<bibRefCitation author="Moure, J. S. &amp; Hurd, P. D." box="[508,769,1580,1607]" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" refId="ref76175" refString="Moure, J. S. &amp; Hurd, P. D. (1987) An Annotated Catalog of the Halictid Bees of the Western Hemisphere (Hymenoptera: Halictidae). Smithsonian Institution Press, Washington, D. C., 405 pp." type="book" year="1987">Moure &amp; Hurd (1987)</bibRefCitation>
transferred it to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Eickwort" authorityYear="1969" box="[970,1147,1580,1606]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Augochlora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Oxystoglossella">
<emphasis box="[970,1147,1580,1606]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Oxystoglossella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, an opinion followed by Moure (2007). However the 
<typeStatus box="[476,524,1617,1643]" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">type</typeStatus>
is probably lost and the identity of this species is uncertain considering only the original description. We did not find any clues about the identity of this species and its generic placement among augochlorines. Nevertheless, 
<bibRefCitation author="Schrottky, C." box="[482,673,1688,1714]" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" pagination="180 - 286" refId="ref76809" refString="Schrottky, C. (1913) La distribucion geografica de los himenopteros argentinos. Anales de La Sociedad Cientifica Argentina, 75, 180 - 286" type="journal article" year="1913">Schrottky (1913)</bibRefCitation>
placed species now allocated in several distinct halictine genera, as 
<taxonomicName box="[151,326,1724,1750]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Augochloropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,326,1724,1750]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Augochloropsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cameron" authorityYear="1903" box="[339,501,1724,1750]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Caenohalictus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[339,501,1724,1750]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Caenohalictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[554,745,1724,1750]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">
<taxonomicName box="[554,741,1724,1750]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Paroxystoglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Paroxystoglossa</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
within his concept of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1853" box="[991,1140,1724,1750]" class="Insecta" family="Hymenoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Oxystoglossa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[991,1140,1724,1750]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Oxystoglossa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. To minimize changes, we keep this species as unplaced within 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1853" box="[563,695,1760,1786]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Augochlora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="lato">
<emphasis box="[563,695,1760,1786]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Augochlora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[702,735,1760,1787]" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" sensu="lato">
<emphasis box="[702,728,1760,1786]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">s.l</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
